<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nadia Davids, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668090732" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Cape Fever</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Simon and Schuster)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Taut plotting, electric prose, and Soraya&#8217;s paranoid first-person narration set this slim, atmospheric novel apart.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263751" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/adam-morgan-john-berryman-tilar-j-mazzeo-and-more-10-new-books-out-today/screen-shot-2025-12-02-at-2-46-12-pm/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM.png" data-orig-size="952,1444" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Three Stories of Forgetting" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-198x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-675x1024.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-263751" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-198x300.png" alt="Three Stories of Forgetting" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-198x300.png 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-675x1024.png 675w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-768x1165.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM-33x50.png 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Screen-Shot-2025-12-02-at-2.46.12-PM.png 952w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Djaimilia Pereira de Almeida, trans. by Alison Entrekin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374612092" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Three Stories of Forgetting</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(FSG)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A haunting exploration of the memories of three men and the reverberations of slavery, colonialism, and empire.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>From the publisher</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="262931" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/berlin-shuffle/berlin-shuffle/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1668,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="berlin shuffle" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-667x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-262931" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-196x300.jpg" alt="berlin shuffle" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/berlin-shuffle-scaled.jpg 1668w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ulrich Alexander Boschwitz, trans. by Philip Boehm, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250869494" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Berlin Shuffle</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Metropolitan Books)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“What Boschwitz saw clearly enough was the utter despoliation of one’s identity, of one’s trust in the world, and ultimately of one’s very humanity.”<br />
<em>–</em>André Aciman</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263755" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/adam-morgan-john-berryman-tilar-j-mazzeo-and-more-10-new-books-out-today/71nujtxfsol-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Everyone in the Group Chat Dies" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-263755" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" alt="Everyone in the Group Chat Dies" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71nujtXFSoL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 652w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>L. M. Chilton, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668094174" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Everyone in the Group Chat Dies</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Gallery Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Chilton offers a sharp, fast-paced, modern twist on the classic murder mystery.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Library Journal</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263752" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/adam-morgan-john-berryman-tilar-j-mazzeo-and-more-10-new-books-out-today/attachment/9781646223152/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152.jpeg" data-orig-size="300,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Best Debut Short Stories 2025" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-263752" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152-200x300.jpeg" alt="Best Debut Short Stories 2025" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9781646223152.jpeg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Edited by Kendall Storey and Elizabeth Pankova, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781646223152" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Best Debut Short Stories 2025</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Catapult)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;The essential annual guide to the newest voices in literature.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>From the publisher</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263753" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/adam-morgan-john-berryman-tilar-j-mazzeo-and-more-10-new-books-out-today/71uscn0mzxl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="699,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Queen Elizabeth II" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-210x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-263753" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-210x300.jpg" alt="Queen Elizabeth II" width="210" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-210x300.jpg 210w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-42x60.jpg 42w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-35x50.jpg 35w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71uScn0MzxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 699w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 210px) 100vw, 210px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>David Cannadine, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780198902300" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Queen Elizabeth II: A Concise Biography of an Exceptional Sovereign</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Oxford University Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;In this masterpiece of distillation and carefully crafted judgements on an extraordinary life lived in turbulent times for her country, her Commonwealth, and her family, David Cannadine brings his special gifts as a biographer and obituarist to every page.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Peter Hennessy</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263754" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/adam-morgan-john-berryman-tilar-j-mazzeo-and-more-10-new-books-out-today/attachment/9798217044931/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931.jpeg" data-orig-size="299,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Spasm, Robin Cook" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-263754" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931-199x300.jpeg" alt="Spasm, Robin Cook" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/9798217044931.jpeg 299w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Robin Cook, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217044931" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Spasm</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Putnam)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Robin Cook, the master of the medical thriller, turns up the tension once again &#8230; Fast-paced and frighteningly relevant.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Out South Florida</em></p>
